function [V]=power(D,param);% powerV                    - power variogram model (Jan 1,2001)%% Compute the power variogram matrix from a distance matrix.%% SYNTAX :%% [V]=powerV(D,param);%% INPUT :%% D       n by m   distance matrix, having real values >=0.% param   1 by 2   vector of parameters such that :%                  param(1) is a slope factor, with 0<param(1)<2.%                  param(2) is the exponent for the power model.%% OUTPUT :%% V       n by m   variogram matrix with same size as D.V=param(1)*(D.^param(2));